Vouch Protocol License Index
============================

The Vouch Protocol project uses a multi-license structure to balance open collaboration, 
permissive adoption, and sustainability.

Please consult the specific license for the component you are using:

1. Protocol Specification (LICENSE-SPEC)
   -------------------------------------
   Path: licenses/LICENSE-SPEC
   License: Community Specification License 1.0
   Applies to: Protocol design, DID format, JWT structure, and verification flow.
   Goal: Open standard implementation rights + patent grants.

2. Client SDK (LICENSE-CLIENT)
   ---------------------------
   Path: licenses/LICENSE-CLIENT
   License: Apache License, Version 2.0
   Applies to: Signer, Keys, Audio, TypeScript SDK, and Client Integration Adapters.
   Goal: Permissive adoption (commercial & open source) for agents using the protocol.

3. Server SDK (LICENSE-SERVER)
   ---------------------------
   Path: licenses/LICENSE-SERVER
   License: GNU Affero General Public License v3.0 (AGPL-3.0)
   Applies to: Verifier, Revocation, Reputation, and Registry components.
   Goal: Ensure improvements to the core trust infrastructure are shared back to the community.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
For more details, see the licenses/ directory.
